theorem compl_frontier_eq_union_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    (frontier A)ᶜ = interior A ∪ interior (Aᶜ) := by
  calc
    (frontier A)ᶜ
        = (closure A \ interior A)ᶜ := by
          simpa [frontier_eq_closure_diff_interior (X := X) (A := A)]
    _ = (closure A)ᶜ ∪ interior A := by
          simpa [Set.compl_diff]
    _ = interior (Aᶜ) ∪ interior A := by
          simpa [interior_compl_eq_compl_closure (X := X) (A := A)]
    _ = interior A ∪ interior (Aᶜ) := by
          simpa [Set.union_comm]

theorem compl_frontier_eq_closure_compl_union_interior
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    (frontier A)ᶜ = (closure A)ᶜ ∪ interior A := by
  classical
  -- First, rewrite the frontier in terms of a set difference.
  have h₁ : frontier A = closure A \ interior A :=
    frontier_eq_closure_diff_interior (X := X) (A := A)
  -- Translate the set difference into an intersection with a complement.
  have h₂ : (closure A \ interior A : Set X) = closure A ∩ (interior A)ᶜ := by
    simp [Set.diff_eq, Set.inter_comm]
  -- Now transform the left‐hand side step‐by‐step.
  calc
    (frontier A)ᶜ
        = (closure A \ interior A)ᶜ := by
          simpa [h₁]
    _ = (closure A ∩ (interior A)ᶜ)ᶜ := by
          simpa [h₂]
    _ = (closure A)ᶜ ∪ ((interior A)ᶜ)ᶜ := by
          simpa [Set.compl_inter]
    _ = (closure A)ᶜ ∪ interior A := by
          simp

theorem compl_frontier_eq_closure_compl_union_interior
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    (frontier A)ᶜ = (closure A)ᶜ ∪ interior A := by
  simpa [frontier_def, Set.compl_diff]

theorem interior_closure_union_closure_right_eq
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    interior (closure (A ∪ closure B)) = interior (closure (A ∪ B)) := by
  -- First, express both closures in terms of `closure A ∪ closure B`.
  have h₁ : closure (A ∪ closure B) = closure A ∪ closure B :=
    closure_union (s := A) (t := closure B)
  have h₂ : closure (A ∪ B) = closure A ∪ closure B :=
    closure_union (s := A) (t := B)
  -- From the two equalities, deduce that the two closures coincide.
  have h : closure (A ∪ closure B) = closure (A ∪ B) := by
    simpa [h₁, h₂.symm]
      using (rfl : (closure A ∪ closure B) = closure A ∪ closure B)
  -- Taking interiors preserves the equality.
  simpa using congrArg (fun s : Set X => interior s) h

theorem compl_frontier_eq_interior_union_interior_compl
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    (frontier A)ᶜ = interior A ∪ interior (Aᶜ) := by
  -- Expand the definition of `frontier` and use basic set identities.
  simpa [frontier, Set.compl_diff, interior_compl_eq_compl_closure,
        Set.union_comm]

theorem compl_frontier_eq_union_interior_compl {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    (A : Set X) :
    (frontier A)ᶜ = interior A ∪ interior (Aᶜ) := by
  -- Rewrite the frontier in terms of `closure` and `interior`.
  have h₁ : frontier A = closure A \ interior A :=
    frontier_eq_closure_diff_interior (X := X) (A := A)
  -- Take complements and apply De Morgan.
  calc
    (frontier A)ᶜ
        = (closure A \ interior A)ᶜ := by
          simpa [h₁]
    _ = (closure A)ᶜ ∪ interior A := by
          simpa using Set.compl_diff
    _ = interior (Aᶜ) ∪ interior A := by
          simpa [interior_compl_eq_compl_closure (X := X) (A := A),
                 Set.union_comm]
    _ = interior A ∪ interior (Aᶜ) := by
          simpa [Set.union_comm]

theorem interior_inter_of_isOpen_left
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} (hA : IsOpen A) :
    interior (A ∩ B) = A ∩ interior B := by
  ext x
  constructor
  · intro hx
    have hAB : x ∈ A ∩ B := interior_subset hx
    have hxA : x ∈ A := hAB.1
    have hxIntB : x ∈ interior B := by
      have hSub : (A ∩ B : Set X) ⊆ B := by
        intro y hy; exact hy.2
      exact (interior_mono hSub) hx
    exact And.intro hxA hxIntB
  · rintro ⟨hxA, hxIntB⟩
    -- Consider the open set `A ∩ interior B` containing `x`.
    have hOpen : IsOpen (A ∩ interior B) := hA.inter isOpen_interior
    have hMem₁ : x ∈ (A ∩ interior B) := And.intro hxA hxIntB
    -- This open set is contained in `A ∩ B`.
    have hSub : (A ∩ interior B : Set X) ⊆ A ∩ B := by
      intro y hy
      exact And.intro hy.1 (interior_subset hy.2)
    -- Hence `A ∩ B` belongs to the neighbourhoods of `x`.
    have hMem₂ : (A ∩ B : Set X) ∈ nhds x :=
      Filter.mem_of_superset (hOpen.mem_nhds hMem₁) hSub
    -- Conclude that `x` is in the interior of `A ∩ B`.
    exact (mem_interior_iff_mem_nhds).2 hMem₂
